<item>
            <title>[LU-14758] dump distributed transaction if it timed out</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14758</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Sometimes lots of update logs are seen, this may be because some distributed transaction failed to commit, and cause all subsequent transaction not able to cancel, thus leave update logs there though they were committed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Such distributed transaction should be dumped to console to help understand what went wrong.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
